  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a criminal offense in most countries worldwide. It is typically covered under criminal legislation and financial crime statutes. Money laundering involves concealing the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through legitimate businesses or financial systems to make it appear legal. Many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations that criminalize such activities, with potential penalties including significant fines and imprisonment.",
